phrases: Does not it seem more crowded than usual?
Apparently, a local festival called the Sasahata Tanabata starts today.
It is all well and good that we got to Hatagaya,
but it looks like there are not many customers at our all-important MgRonald's.
This cannot be good for them.
Bad place for a lovers' quarrel.
If the place is not crowded, it could get really ugly if things go wrong.
Also, what if the man's in the right?
We could end up ruining things for him at work when it was not even his fault.
Fortunately, there is a Sentucky right in front of us.
Let us have a strategy meeting there first!
It all starts right here, right now
Let us picture what we can do
Let us picture what we can do
Let us picture what we can do
But we can overcome them all
But we can overcome them all
But we can overcome them all
Our dreams are born from nothing
And take us to that shining sky
And take us to that shining sky
And take us to that shining sky
And take us to that shining sky
I want to spread my wings
Now here I go, with the greatest smile on my face
Now here I go, with the greatest smile on my face
Now here I go, with the greatest smile on my face
Now here I go, with the greatest smile on my face
Let us set out to an unknown world
Let us set out to an unknown world
Let us set out to an unknown world
Let us set out to an unknown world
We will be the ones to choose and decide the future
Let us chase after our dreams
There will be times when we cry
I have a really important wish
I am sure you will be able to meet your future self
I am sure you will be able to meet your future self
I am sure you will be able to meet your future self
First, tell me everything there is to know about this Maou guy.
Maybe we can use that information to resolve this fight.
As long as I am the Hero and he is the Overlord,
the only thing we can do is fight.
I wonder how she plans on clearing up the misunderstanding Rika has.
I will have an iced coffee.
I will have the maple biscuit and iced tea combo, then.
If you like, please take this coupon we are giving away as part of our grand opening promotion.
We shall put all our heart into preparing your order.
I am sure our items are simply thrilled to serve and be served to you lovely ladies.
I have committed a grave sin in making a lady like you wait!
Guys like that surprisingly suck at playing around
and because all kinds of problems for themselves, right?
His perfume and shades are in bad taste too.
Let us hear how things ended up this way.
Let me hear it straight from the horses' mouths.
Well, he is a good neighbor...
I want you to kill Overlord Satan with me
That is what she said before,
but now he is a good neighbor?
He is someone I want to kill as soon as possible.
But I know you are not being honest with yourself, Emi.
There is nothing going on between Maou and me.
I wanted to keep Suzuno away from him for a completely different reason.
It is not like we are fighting over him or anything!
That is why I said you are not being honest with yourself.
Why do you even want to pair me and Maou up so badly?
Just thinking about it makes me mad.
That cruel, sneaky lump of avarice!
He is thick-skinned, broke as hell,
and the kind of absurd man who would try to make someone feel indebted to him
by lending them an umbrella he just picked up somewhere!
I cannot let that slide, Yusa!
Ashiya sure is taking his sweet time.
You want me to go and stuff myself with Sentucky's fried chicken?
Well you do not have to stuff yourself...
Telling me to go to the supermarket in front of the station
and stuff myself with the 88Y per 100g bargain buckets of fried chicken would be one thing,
but we do not have the financial leeway to fill the coffers of Sentucky, a potential enemy!
We need to do this because they could end up being our enemy.
To defeat the enemy, you must first know the enemy.
You could not possibly have forgotten these words, right?
Your job is not just to eat.
You must eat as much as possible.
Learn their strengths, weaknesses, and everything in between.
This is the price we must pay to climb the corporate ladder.
I, Ashiya Shirou, will keep expenses to a minimum as I thoroughly investigate them.
Okay, I did say to learn everything, but you are taking way too long!
So, we are done with our usual jobs.
but I suppose that is only natural.
Things outside have gotten pretty lively thanks to the festival.
However, compared to our enemy, Sentucky,
We cannot afford to keep sitting on our asses.
Maybe we should stand outside and try to attract customers?
but it would be best to wait until Ashiya makes his report.
What would we even attract them with?
Until he gets here, my hands are tied.
Should I just make a move now?
If I made my move now...
I cannot see it at all!
I cannot predict what will happen on this fast-food battlefront!
I never knew it would be this deep!
I know you are the shift supervisor, but you do not have to do everything yourself.
I am the commander of this army!
Me panicking here will only because anxiety among my subordinates!
This is not the time to make our move.
The flow of battle may be in the enemy's favor right now,
but gentlemen, our time fast approaches!
We need only bide our time!
Wait, where were you even hiding all this time?
I noticed you when you came in, but I wanted to stay out of trouble.
However, after hearing you slander Milord, I had no choice but to speak!
This is a good opportunity, Ashiya.
This is something that will affect your and Maou's honor.
Why do I need to help you out?
I am guessing you are here to research this place.
I will treat you to whatever you want.
I did not expect you to be this greedy.
Do not get the wrong idea.
What I need to prioritize most right now is our finances.
I will endure any kind of humiliation to that end,
even if it means I must cover myself in dirt for it.
Anyway, I could not research the dessert and salads because I would have gone over my budget.
I will just order that later.
I do not really get it, but...
If I must specify some kind of relationship with the people here,
then I will say that I am Kamazuki's neighbor.
I am Suzuki Rika, Emi's colleague.
Wait, you said you were Suzuno's neighbor.
Does that mean you live with Maou?
I want to ask you about him because I want to know him better.
You do not have to be on guard.
there is a man Emi does not want another girl getting close to.
Yusa, what exactly is going on here?
That is what I want to know.
A man Yusa does not want another girl getting close to, huh?
It will affect our honor, huh?
This is what they call letting the cat out of the bag, Yusa.
This will be the first Kamazuki hears of this too,
but Maou and I used to run a company in the past.
What on earth is he on about?
Wait, you do not look all that different from us.
Our company was primarily a real estate and personnel placement agency.
We also dabbled in construction sometimes.
Your previous job was related to construction work?
Wait, how old are you, again?
W-Well, how should I put it...
If I remember correctly, were not you a temp at the time?
So the Hero's just a temp.
Our operations were pretty large in scale,
but we were still small enough that we proprietors needed to take command out on the field.
Not only was Yusa talented, she also had backup from her firm.
We were all youngsters without much work experience.
We were smack-dab in the middle of a recession back then,
so if a bunch of big contracts were taken away
from a firm that was run by upstarts like us, it would crumble and fall.
And the last person we competed with over a contract
We lost the contract, and our company went bankrupt.
We drifted from place to place until we reached Sasazuka.
Roughly a year after we would seen her last,
we ran into Yusa again by chance!
I guess Yusa had us, her ex-business rivals, on her mind.
She stops by from time to time to see how we are doing.
However, Maou has not given up on being a successful businessman!
Right now, he is working his pants off at MgRonald's in order to learn about business administration
In just a year, he is become a shift supervisor.
I take care of things around the house.
We hope to run a business under Maou someday!
I want to support that with all I have got!
But business is just a gamble, so to speak.
If Yusa wants to keep Kamazuki away from us
so that she does not get mixed up in our gambles,
I am in far too deep to ever get out, though.
He still sees Yusa as his enemy and hates her.
I do not think things are like what you think they are.
You are not that much older than me.
I am ashamed of myself for letting my imagination run wild and poking my nose into this.
Emi, you should have just said so from the start.
I did, but you paid no heed to me.
My family runs a small factory,
and whenever we were in real trouble, we all worked together to get through it.
but this Maou eats the food you make,
sleeps on the mattress you air out, and puts on underwear that you wash, right?
That means you are supporting everyone.
You should be more proud of yourself.
You guys are close enough to help each other out like that,
so I am sure things'll go well for you!
You are the first person to say anything like that.
I feel a little better now.
That is what I want to ask.
I guess everyone has their own history.
Anyway, that cleared up your misunderstanding, right?
Now I kind of want to see this Maou guy for personal reasons.
If he has real talent, then I should get to know him for the sake of my own future as well.
You have your scouting report to make too, do not you?
How about we head over together?
Anyway, get me a maple biscuit and salad to go.
I must thank Kamazuki for all she is done for us too.
Why did it end up like this?!
Things are getting worse and worse.
It will make your food taste most foul.
No matter how much one worries,
things will change with time, whether one likes it or not.
I hope you do not have any regrets when things do not go your way.
That is the first time a Sentucky employee has stuck his nose in my business.
My, that was very rude of me,
It is in a man's nature to take advantage of women when they are at their weakest.
What is that supposed to mean?
Also, from what I have seen,
their main attraction, the fried chicken...
Well, it depends on the type,
but shockingly, you can even eat the bones!
Wait, who even wants to eat bones?
Did you just say ogre-nic coffee?!
I am talking about organic cultivation.
However, I do not think there is much of a difference otherwise.
The service was nothing out of the ordinary, either.
The only possibility left is that the passersby are getting distracted by the new place.
Anyway, we will not go down without a fight.
Your words are wasted on me!
allow me to contribute to your sales.
with large drinks and fries, please.
Urushihara will probably bitch and whine,
but let us go with this for tonight's dinner.
you have my permission to knock his lights out.
I do not really get it, though.
Also, his professional spirit is off the charts!
There are lots of capable people around you, Emi.
Oh, can I count myself in that number too?
The chairs here are harder than Sentucky's.
Could you take a seat after placing your order, please?
Okay, then get me a small iced coffee.
You can help yourself to that.
Then I will order an apple pie too.
Be grateful and bring it here.
You are not as charismatic as I expected you to be.
This place is a ghost town during the shift you are supervising too.
And what do you think you are saying?
Who the hell do you think you are?!
I will send a complaint to your HQ about the terrible way you are treating me.
Even customers need to play by the restaurant's rules.
I heard about you from these two and Ashiya.
Let us just say Ashiya and Emi have very different views of you.
I had to see for myself what you are like.
I have no idea what you are saying,
but are you one of those busybodies?
Customers are not showing up, and now Emi's here...
You cannot be like that, Maou.
An iced coffee and a fresh apple pie!
You had to do this because I was dealing with Maou.
Looks like you are working hard, Chiho.
Are you a friend of Yusa's, madam?
Yusa's been helping me out a lot.
What do you think you are doing?
You are surrounded by way too many amazing people!
Well-mannered, with the right outlook toward work...
This has to be against the rules!
What are you, a middle-aged drunk?!
I do not really know what happened, though...
What are you going to do from now on?
You went and told Ashiya that you would not go down without a fight.
What I want to see is how you work.
there are a bunch of talented people around Emi.
Following that, you cannot be as dim as you look.
So I look dim, do I?
Wait, it is not just your looks, but your brain too?
We will take them on with flyers!
Would you like a hamburger at MgRonald's?
In that case, let us show off how our stuff is easy to eat since it is boneless!
Would you like a Big Mag?
It is boneless, so it is really easy to eat!
Why would not a burger be boneless?
You sure say some funny things.
Now that it is come to this,
I think it is time we start letting people who are not customers use the washroom too.
I am only doing this'because you asked.
Please, it is perfectly all right!
Let me treat you to something.
Nah, I delivered what I had to,
and my wife made dinner for me, so I will pass.
Wow, we got a great one!
Let us decorate it before the dinnertime rush!
Okay, then let us use the flyers.
Can we really use these as decorations?
Since the Sasahata Tanabata festival's going on,
Maou came up with the idea of letting people write their wishes on strips of paper
and do the Tanabata decorations themselves.
He asked the manager to get HQ to approve his idea of giving people
who made the decorations a small soda for free.
He met Mr. Watanabe, the old man from earlier, while doing community service
and asked him for some of his bamboo.
Of course, we do not know if this will get us anywhere,
but at least it is changed the mood here, right?
I will admit he is enthusiastic about work.
Is this the place with the cute and funny girl?
Mom, I want to put one up!
How did this many people show up just because they put out some bamboo?!
What kind of feng shui is this?!
Those who have decided on your orders,
There are some empty seats over there.
Where in this silent sky does the sun rise?
A promise I made while pretending to not see it
Being a liar and a coward
If I was at fault for everything
Then our promise might only have been a fleeting dream
I managed to hide it in the shadow of the moonlight
My tears will not flow anymore
If I was able to let everything go
I might be able to cry again
But this world is full of things I want to protect
